A Kenyan opposition politician says he is still detained in a
toilet at the country's main airport after he refused an attempt to deport him.A lawyer for Miguna Miguna, James Orengo, says authorities are in
contempt after the High Court on Tuesday ordered his immediate release and a
court appearance on Wednesday morning.Miguna was deported to Canada last month in a crackdown on
politicians who attended the mock inauguration of opposition leader Raila
Odinga to protest President Uhuru Kenyatta's re-election. A court later ordered
